<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 15:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Israel to Step up Bilateral Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and Israel have decided to
strengthen cooperation in the fields of tourism, business and
technology.
</P>
<P>
This was stressed by Cypriot Minister of Trade, Industry and
Tourism Nicos Rolandis on Monday, after a meeting with Israeli
Ambassador to Cyprus Semi Tzur.
</P>
<P>
Rolandis said Israeli tourists travelling to Cyprus are on the
rise. "In the first five months of this year Israeli tourists
increased fourfold, in comparison to last year," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We are expecting 80,000 to 90,000 (Israeli tourists) this
year, whereas last year around 50,000 Israelis visited Cyprus,"
the Cypriot minister added.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli ambassador said Cyprus has become an attraction to
Israeli tourists and their number is growing monthly and daily.
</P>
<P>
Referring to business and technological cooperation between the
two countries, Tzur said Rolandis will soon visit his country to
advance cooperation in the high technology sector.
</P>
<P>
A Cypriot government delegation recently visited Israel and was
optimistic about the future of technological cooperation between
the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Israeli businessmen dealing in the high technology area, on
the other hand, are interested in investing in Cyprus together
with Cypriot businessmen, because of the island's relations with
the European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
