<DOCNO> XIE19980804.0003 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Waiting for Indonesia's True Action to Protect Ethnic Chinese: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan said here Monday that China is now waiting for the result
of the investigation and further action of the Indonesian
government on the brutalities against ethnic Chinese during the
riots in May.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government is greatly concerned with the situation
of the ethnic Chinese and Chinese nationals living in Indonesia,
Tang told reporters at the airport upon his arrival here Monday
evening after visiting the Philippines and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Tang said the Chinese government attaches great importance to
the incidents in Indonesia and demanded through diplomatic
channels on many occasions the Indonesian side seriously punish
the rioters who committed the brutalities.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government also called on the Indonesian side to
take forceful and effective measures to safeguard the personal
safety and legitimate rights and interests of the ethnic Chinese
and Chinese nationals in Indonesia, and prevent such incidents
from recurrence.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that during the riots that took place in some cities
in Indonesia in May, many shops owned by Chinese Indonesians were
ransacked and burned and many ethnic Chinese women were savagely
raped.
</P>
<P>
"It is natural that these criminal acts have sparked grave
concern and strong indignation among the people in China and the
overseas Chinese societies," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said that all the staff of the Chinese
embassy in Indonesia worked around the clock and followed closely
the developments of the situation.
</P>
<P>
They also took risk to help many ethnic Chinese and Chinese
nationals out of danger, Tang said, adding that the Chinese
ambassador made solemn representations many times to the
Indonesian Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Tang said, the spokesman of the Chinese Foreign
Ministry clearly stated the position of the Chinese government
time and again.
</P>
<P>
Not long ago, Tang said, he addressed the issue of the ethnic
Chinese and Chinese nationals living in Indonesia when he attended
the ASEAN Regional Forum meeting in Manila and he also discussed
the issue with Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali Alatas.
</P>
<P>
Tang noted on those occasions that the Chinese Indonesians have
worked hard for many decades and have made indelible contributions
to Indonesia's economic development and social progress.
</P>
<P>
When the Indonesian economy is in serious trouble after the
East Asian financial crisis, the ethnic Chinese are still making
unremitting efforts to help lift that country out of the economic
predicament and maintain its social stability, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
The status of the ethnic Chinese should be respected and their
personal safety and legitimate rights and interests should be
fully protected. They should be treated the same as all Indonesian
citizens, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
Tang strongly demanded the Indonesian government take the
incidents seriously and take effective measures as soon as
possible to safeguard the personal safety and legitimate rights
and interests of the ethnic Chinese and Chinese nationals and
severely punish those held accountable.
</P>
<P>
Tang quoted Alatas as saying that such incidents are a shame
for Indonesia and that Indonesian President B.J. Habibie also
admitted the incidents as "the most inhuman event."
</P>
<P>
Habibie has ordered the establishment of a special
investigation committee on the incident, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia has pledged that it will punish the rioters and take
necessary measures to prevent such incidents from happening again,
Tang said.
</P>
<P>
"We are now waiting to see what results the special
investigation committee will announce and what conclusions it will
 come to," Tang told the reporters.
</P>
<P>
"We are also watching closely what forceful and effective
measures the Indonesian side will take to safeguard the personal
safety and legitimate rights and interests of the ethnic Chinese
and Chinese nationals in Indonesia and to prevent the recurrence
of such incidents," Tang noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
