<DOCNO> XIE19980804.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi King Undergoes Successful Colon Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Saudi King Fahd Ibn
Abdul-Aziz Monday has undergone a successful colon operation, the
Saudi Royal Palace announced.
</P>
<P>
The palace was quoted by official Saudi Press Agency (SPA) as
saying in a statement that King Fahd was suffering from an
inflamed colon which was successfully treated.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the king was feeling well after the
surgery. He would remain in hospital for a few days for
recuperation, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi monarch was admitted to King Faisal Specialist
Hospital in Riyadh Sunday for medical tests. He traveled from the
Red Sea city of Jeddah, where he usually spends his summer
holidays.
</P>
<P>
King Fahd, 77, was admitted in hospital last March for
treating an infection on the gall bladder.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, he suffered from a health setback caused by fatigue
and stress, and upon the doctors' advice spent a three-month
period of recuperation, during which the state affairs were
managed by Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz.
</P>
<P>
King Fahd, who took power in 1982, is the fifth monarch of
Saudi Arabia, which was founded by his late father, Abdul-Aziz
Al-Saud in 1931. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
