<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Sets up Fine Arts Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The National Ethiopian Fine
Arts and Media Award Enterprise was established here Monday to
foster competition among artists and journalists by awarding
prizes to those who exhibit excellence in their professions.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the founding conference, Ethiopian Minister of
Information and Culture, Wolde-Michael Chemu, said increased
attention should be given to artists and media personnel who play
a significant role in the socio-economic, political and cultural
spheres.
</P>
<P>
The minister said many countries worldwide recognize and
appreciate the contribution of artists and media men in enhancing
the physical and spiritual wellbeing of the community at large.
</P>
<P>
He said that government of various countries, developed and
underdeveloped alike, offer awards and incentives for creative
individuals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
