<HEADLINE> African Miners to Meet in Morocco </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 3 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on "investment and
business opportunities in the African mining sector" will be held
in Morocco in November, it is learned here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The forum to be held in Marrakech, Morocco, from November 16
to 18, would mobilize private capital into the region to invest
in mineral development and exploration, the Committee of Southern
African Development Community (SADC) ministers responsible for
mining said in a statement here.
</P>
<P>
It said the region's contribution to the world mineral supply
was declining although the potential mineral supply was
significant.
</P>
<P>
"Mobilizing private capital in the region to invest in mineral
development and exploration could be achieved through increased
investment in mineral exploration and mining development," the
committee said.
</P>
<P>
It noted the availability of public and private sector
financing windows from the african development bank which was
providing facilities to small, medium and large scale
enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
