<HEADLINE> Britain to Host Conference on Fighting Child Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The British government announced
Monday it is to host an international conference on fighting
against various kinds of child abuse in early October.
</P>
<P>
British Foreign Office minister Derek Fatchett said in a
statement issued early Monday that London will stage this
"ground-breaking" ASEM (Asia-Europe Meeting) on child exploitation
on October 6-8.
</P>
<P>
"We need a real international program to tackle the dreadful
problem -- a problem that known no borders. The conference will
move the process from mere discussion to agreeing practical
action," Fatchett said.
</P>
<P>
"We aim to show that by working together across the boundaries
of our regions we can contend with these problems and make a real
difference to children and their families," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The aim of the London conference is to agree practical steps
to fight the commercial exploitation of children in Asia and
Europe, protect children from abuse, reintegrate victims into
society and improve cooperation between states," he added.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day conference, health experts from Asian and
European 25 countries, representatives from charities,
international children's organizations and the private sector will
work together to resolve this serious problem.  
</P>
