<HEADLINE> Talks Between UNSCOM, Iraq Break Down, Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The ongoing talks on weapons
inspection between the U.N. chief arms inspector Richard Butler
and Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz broke down, a
U.N. source told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that such a thing happened in the
history of the relationship between Iraq and UNSCOM (the
U.N. Special Commission on disarmament in Iraq), which indicates
that their relations are worsening.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. source told Xinhua that the talks broke down soon
after the second round of talks between UNSCOM headed by Butler
and Iraqi side headed by Aziz started.
</P>
<P>
Then Butler made a phone call to the President of the Security
Council and informed the Security Council of the current
situation, said the U.N. source who spoke on condition of
anonymity. 
</P>
