<HEADLINE> Arafat to Announce new Cabinet Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 3 (Xinhua) -- President of the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) is to present the new cabinet to the
Palestinian Legislative Council (PLC) for approval on Wednesday,
PLC Press Office said in Ramallah on Monday.
</P>
<P>
During Wednesday's PLC special session in Ramallah, President
Arafat will present to the Council the new cabinet, and possibly a
ministerial statement, and after discussions the PLC will vote on
the new cabinet, the Office said.
</P>
<P>
The PLC has been demanding changes in Arafat's cabinet since
last summer, because of suspicions of corruption by PNA
ministries.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen of Arafat's 18 cabinet ministers offered their
resignations a year ago under pressure from legislators, but
Arafat took no action at the time.
</P>
<P>
Only in January this year did Arafat announce that he would
carry out a cabinet reshuffle. On June 24, he announced that he
accepted the year-old resignations and asked for some time to
carry out the changes.
</P>
<P>
Arafat then carried out political consulations with different
political parties and invited them to join the new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Arafat is said to invite some economic experts and academics to
join his new cabinet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
