<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-03 18:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt, Kuwait to Boost Information Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Egypt and Kuwait Monday signed a
protocol on promoting bilateral cooperation in the field of
information, Egypt's Middle East News Agency (MENA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Signed by the Egyptian Minister of Information Safwat el-Sherif
and visiting Kuwaiti Minister of Information Yusef Mohammad Al
Sumait, the protocol provides for production and exchange of radio
and TV programs and exchange of visits by media people.
</P>
<P>
In the news sector, the two sides agreed to extend facilities
to correspondents, intensify media coverage and make use of news
services of Egyptian and Kuwaiti TV satellite stations.
</P>
<P>
The protocol proposed a weekly joint and live cast on "Good
Morning Egypt and "Good Morning Kuwait" programs and on their
radio.
</P>
<P>
It also urged MENA and the Kuwaiti News Agency to take further
steps to enhance cooperation between them.
</P>
<P>
The two sides decided on the formation of a joint committee of
leading radio, TV and satellite stations personnel under the
chairmanship of the Egyptian Radio and Television Union.
</P>
<P>
The committee is to meet on a bi-annual basis in both countries
to follow up cooperation in various domains and present progress
reports in this respect to respective minister of information.
</P>
<P>
After the signing ceremony, Sherif said the protocol embodies a
model for an integral Arab information system.
</P>
<P>
Sumait, on his part, said the two countries were embarking on a
phase of professional media integration based on clear and solid
mechanisms.
</P>
<P>
Sumait left Cairo Monday after a three-day visit to Egypt and
headed for Damascus to continue his regional tour to Syria and
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
During the Cairo trip, the minister met with President Hosni
Mubarak and conveyed to him a verbal message from Kuwaiti Emir
Sheikh Jaber al-Ahmed al-Sabah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
