<HEADLINE> Three More Opposition Representatives Join Tajik Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov
on Monday appointed three more opposition representatives to the
cabinet, bringing the total posts held by opposition
representatives to 10.
</P>
<P>
Under a decree signed by Rakhmonov, Shodi Kabirov will head the
Ministry of Agriculture, while field commanders Makhmadruzi
Davlatov and Salamsho Mukhabatov will be heads of the committee
for emergencies and civil defense and the committee for oil and
gas respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency quoted Rakhmonov's spokesman, Zafar
Saidov, as saying that opposition representatives had earlier
accepted the posts of first vice-premier, minister of economics
and foreign economic relations, and the chairman of the customs
committee.
</P>
<P>
According to the 30 percent quota envisaged by the General
Agreement on the Establishment of Peace and National Accord,
signed in June, 1997, four more government posts are open to
opposition representatives, Itar-Tass said.
</P>
<P>
The four positions would be discussed during a meeting of the
country's leaders and the Commission for National Reconciliation,
which is headed by leader of the United Tajik opposition Said
Abdullo Nuri.  
</P>
</TEXT>
