<HEADLINE> Portugal to Build Judge Training Center for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Jose Jardim, Portuguese Judicial
Minister said Monday that Portugal would like to cooperate with
Mozambique in building a training center for judges in the
southern African country.
</P>
<P>
Jardim made the statement here after his meeting with his
Mozambican counterpart, Jose Abudo.
</P>
<P>
Jardim said the building of the judges' training center would
be done under the support of such international organizations as
the United Nations Development Program.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese minister said he has offered a package of
proposals to help Mozambique in its legal system building, which
will start from sending Portuguese judges to Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Jardim said his government is willing to get involved in
Mozambique's law revision program, saying that Portugal is
financially guaranteed with this intention.
</P>
<P>
Abudo disclosed that the Judicial Information and Document
Center Portugal has helped built in the country is expected to go
into operation next year.
</P>
<P>
He said it would be very good to have in each county a judge
or prosecutor with college education background.
</P>
<P>
Jardim arrived here Monday for a three-day visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
