<HEADLINE> S. African, U.S. Vice Presidents to Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 3 (Xinhua) -- South African Deputy
President Thabo Mbeki will leave for the United States Tuesday
for bilateral talks with U.S. Vice President Al Gore, Mbeki's
office announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki and Gore, co-chairmen of the U.S.-South African
Bi-national Commission, will meet in a regular session of the
commission following its postponement in February this year
because of the situation in Iraq, the office said.
</P>
<P>
