<HEADLINE> U.S. Appoints Special Envoy to SADC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The United States
ambassador to Botswana, Robert Krueger, has been appointed his
country's special representative to the Southern African
Development Community (SADC).
</P>
<P>
South African Press Association (SAPA) Monday quoted the U.S.
Information Service as saying that the newly-created position
formed part of an initiative by U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright to enhance U.S. links with SADC.
</P>
<P>
"The appointment of ambassador Krueger as the secretary's
special representative signals the growing importance the U.S.
attaches to its ties with the dynamic southern African region,"
the U.S. Information Service said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
But SAPA did not say when the statement was released.
</P>
<P>
A U.S.-SADC forum would also be set up for regular
consultations between the two sides. It would be launched later
in the year.
</P>
<P>
Krueger will retain his post as ambassador to Botswana.
</P>
