<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taliban Claim Capture of Another Province in Northern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's Islamic Taliban
militia Tuesday continued advance in northern Afghanistan and
captured another province of Sar-e-pol, a Taliban official said.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban forces made advance from two fronts -- Qliazar and
Tashkurghan -- and overran Sar-e-pol, located between Faryab and
Jowzjan provinces, said Saeedur Rehman, Taliban's diplomat in
Pakistan, reported the private News Network International (NNI).
</P>
<P>
However, the Taliban official did not give any figures of
casualties on both sides during the offensive, NNI said.
</P>
<P>
No independent confirmation was immediately available.
</P>
<P>
Sar-e-pol was previously held by forces loyal to warlord Rashid
Dostum, one of the strongmen in the anti-Taliban northern
alliance.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, the student militia captured Dostum's native
stronghold of Shiberghan, capital of Jowzjan province, and are
poised to march on Mazar-e-Sharif, around 12 km east of
Shiberghan.
</P>
<P>
Mazar-e-Sharif is the headquarters of the northern alliance
composed of forces led by Dostum, former Afghan military chief
Ahmad Masood and Shiite Hezb-e-Wadhat.
</P>
<P>
After capturing Sar-e-pol, the Taliban have blocked the way of
the alliance forces' attack on Shiberghan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
