<HEADLINE> Wuhan Raises 10 Million Yuan for Flood Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- This capital of central China's
Hubei Province which is fighting the worst floods in four decades
raised more 10 million yuan from 142 local businesses and
institutions today in flood relief fund.
</P>
<P>
Local farmers have been hit the hardest by the floods as they
come on a time when early rice is waiting to be reaped and late
rice to be planted. It is estimated that the floods have caused at
least one billion yuan in direct losses.
</P>
<P>
The local government has appropriated more than 6.2 million
yuan for disaster relief, as well as large amounts of tents, foods
and daily essentials, and resettled 140,000 flood victims.
</P>
<P>
It is also reported that the city's leading officials each
donated 500 yuan for flood victims today.
</P>
<P>
On the middle reaches of the Yangtze River, Wuhan with a
population of seven million today has thrived as a traffic and
business hub in central China thanks to its geographical
position.
</P>
<P>
However, this same geographical position has meant an unending
combat against the floods for the city since the day it came into
being centuries ago. 
</P>
