<HEADLINE> East China Provinces Battle Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu and Anhui
provinces are engaged in a massive effort to battle Yangtze River
flooding and rescue stranded residents.
</P>
<P>
Water levels in the lower reaches of the river continue to rise
and are exerting even greater pressure on levees in east China's
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu has mobilized 820,000 officials, residents, soldiers,
and members of armed police units in the flood control
effort. Rescue teams have evacuated some 25,582 stranded residents.
</P>
<P>
The Yangtze River section in Anhui Province has experienced the
worst flooding this decade resulting from heavy rainfall since
June 26. The provincial government has distributed flood relief
funds totalling 24 million yuan flood over the past 40 days alone.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the provincial flood control and drought relief
department has dispatched thousands of officials and provided
massive shipments of relief materials and equipment, including
3,200 motor vehicles, 2,100 boats, 90 tons of food, 2,300 tents
and thousands of life preservers to the flood ravaged areas.
</P>
<P>
More 200,000 stranded Anhui residents have been evacuated, with
no reported deaths or serious injuries.  
</P>
