<HEADLINE> Guangdong Provincial Procurators Visit HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A nine-member delegation from
the Guangdong Provincial People's Procuratorate (GDPP) led by
Chief Procurator Zhang Xuejun Tuesday began a five-day visit to
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
The delegation had a meeting with Lily Yam Kwan Pui-ying,
commissioner of the Independent Commission Against Corruption
(ICAC) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting the two sides agreed to continue to strengthen
cooperation in fighting cross-boundary corruption more
effectively.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that the GDPP and the ICAC have enjoyed good
cooperation in the past and the visit has allowed both parties to
enhance understanding of each other's work, and to exchange
information on the latest developments of the two organizations.
</P>
<P>
Yam and heads of the ICAC's three departments briefed the
delegation on the SAR's anti-corruption work after Hong Kong's
return to China and the latest corruption scene.
</P>
<P>
Yam noted that the Central Government had pledged full support
for Hong Kong's fight against corruption.
</P>
<P>
"Since Hong Kong's reunification with the mainland, the ICAC
and GDPP, under the framework of 'one country, two systems', have
been able to build on the good relationship developed over the
past ten years or so, and have intensified cooperation in mutual
assistance in investigations," she said.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting both sides agreed that regular meetings
between the two agencies in the future would be useful in
strengthening working relationship, and stressed the importance of
stepping up cooperation, exchanging investigation techniques and
sharing corruption prevention experience.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the ICAC, the GDPP delegation will also call on the
Department of Justice, Security Bureau, Correctional Services
Department and the Police before leaving Saturday. 
</P>
