<HEADLINE> Chinese Army's Pan Yi Banned for Six Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- First division team Chinese
Army's player Pan Yi was banned from competition for six games and
fined for 3,000 Yuan (about 380 U.S. dollars) for kicking his
rival in a match last Sunday, the Chinese Football Association (CF
A) announced here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the first division league victory over Beijing Guo'an in
Shijiazhuang, Pan kicked a Guo'an player who had already fell on
the field, CFA said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Army club was also fined for 1,500 Yuan (about 190
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The suspension means that Pan will be sidelined from the 16th
to the 19th round matches in the first division league and will be
also missing in two legs of the third round of the CFA Cup.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Army has always been on the verge of relegation this
season, standing on the 12th place in the 14-team first division
league after 15 rounds competition. 
</P>
