<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Grants Humanitarian Aid to Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission on
Tuesday approved a humanitarian aid worth 1.95 million ECU (2.145
million U.S. dollars) for Peru.
</P>
<P>
The aid, to be managed by the European Community Humanitarian
Office, will facilitate four non-governmental organizations from
Spain, Britain and the Netherlands in their aid programs in the
southern American country.
</P>
<P>
The commission fund will be used to assist those returning to
their homes after being displaced.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of thousands of people fled during the violence that
has affected Peru for over 12 years and many of them, however, are
returning but having great difficulty resettling on the land that
was abandoned for so long.
</P>
<P>
Commission officials said that funds to help returnees are
scarce in a country where main efforts were being made to grapple
with the effects of the El Nino freak weather patterns that had
caused floods and torrential rains.
</P>
<P>
The fund will assist an eight-month program to be implemented
by Oxfam of Britain, the Red Cross and the International
Solidarity, both of Spain, and the Medics Without Boundaries of
the Netherlands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
