<HEADLINE> Fuel Depot Fire Causes Heavy Damage in Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A furious fire burst out Monday in a
fuel depot located in the Kharhov District of Kiev, capital of
Ukraine, burning one person, twelve oil tanks, an oil truck and
some living facilities nearby.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian Interfax news agency reported that the fire
occurred at 6:40 p.m.(local time) on Monday when a staff member
violated the operational rules in his injection of oil from an oil
tank into an oil truck.
</P>
<P>
The fire was put out until 1:30 a.m. Tuesday morning. Rolling
smoke from the fire could be seen ten kilometers away from the
spot.
</P>
<P>
The first seven months this year have witnessed 21,2000 fires in
Ukraine, five percent down from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The fires had caused a direct economic loss of 12 million
hryvina (about 5.7 million U.S. dollars). Fire victims totaled
1065 people, 68 of whom were children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
