<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tang Shubei on Lin Ti-chuan Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Tang Shubei, executive
vice-president of the Association for Relations Across the Taiwan
Strait (Arats), said today that the unfortunate death of Lin
Ti-chuan from Taiwan resulted from an alleged business dispute
must be dealt with soberly and rationally.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his deep regret and shock at Lin's death, Tang said
that the perpetrators must be apprehended at the earliest possible
date. He also pointed out the cooperation of Lin's family is a
must for obtaining further evidence.
</P>
<P>
The family has agreed to cooperate in related efforts, said
Tang, adding that concerned departments will honor the family's
wishes and return Lin's remains to Taiwan as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Tang said Arats dispatched a deputy secretary general to
Haicheng, a city in northeast China's Liaoning Province,
immediately after reports of the incident to assist local
departments in maintaining close contacts and assisting Lin's
family members from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Chinese people abhor incidents of this
nature, but pointed out the similar cases are common throughout
the world.
</P>
<P>
The case must be dealt with soberly and rationally, said Tang,
noting that constant vigilance must be maintained to prevent
someone from sabotaging cross-Straits relations by taking
advantage of the unfortunate incident.
</P>
<P>
Tang pointed to the proposed mainland tour by Koo Chen-fu,
president of the Taiwan-based Straits Exchange Foundation (Sef),
in mid-September or mid-October, and expressed hope the visit will
proceed in line with suggestions tabled by the Taiwan side.
</P>
<P>
The visit will provide Arats President Wang Daohan and Koo
Chen-fu with an excellent opportunity to freely and fully exchange
views concerning cross-Straits relations, according to Tang. He
also expressed hope that the Taiwan side will refrain from
creating obstacles and strictly adhere to its suggestions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
