<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 6 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday closed with a minimal
rise of 6.59 points at 3,119.54 as compared to Monday's close of
3,112.95.
</P>
<P>
The national index closed at 1,379.05, showing a minor gain of
0.86 points over the previous close of 1,378.19.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 ended marginally higher at 317.26 points and the
U.S. dollar index at 124.14 points as compared to 316.93 and
124.01 respectively.
</P>
<P>
In lackluster trading, equities moved in a very narrow range
and closed with minor gains on balance on scattered support at the
stock market in Bombay Tuesday. 
</P>
