<HEADLINE> Local Residents Express Concern Over Death of Taiwan Woman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- "Taiwan compatriots come here
for business and their legitimate rights should be protected,"
according to Jiang Fenghe, a farmer from Haicheng, northwest
China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Jiang was referring to unfortunate death of Lin Ti-chuan, a
Taiwanese citizen who recently died in the city as a result of
alleged foul play.
</P>
<P>
The hoary-headed farmer visited the city hospital this
morning and happened to encounter the grieving parents of Lin
Ti-chuan.
</P>
<P>
"I'm a parent and fully understand the feelings of
Lin's parents," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
The local farmer learned of the death from TV news report and
learned that local law enforcement officials are expanding efforts
to trace the perpetrators. "I hope those bad guys will be caught
as soon as possible," said Jiang."
</P>
<P>
Lin Ti-chuan's parents attended a traditional memorial service
for their daughter this morning at the city hospital.
</P>
<P>
A young taxi driver said that his family is greatly concerned
about the incident. However, he pointed out that solving the case
will be extremely difficult as Haicheng is a highly mobile city
with a large transient population. Nonetheless, he expressed full
confidence that local law enforcement departments will bring the
case to a quick conclusion.
</P>
<P>
"We're all saddened by Lin's death. However, we're all Chinese
and I sincerely hope the incident will not harm cross-Straits
relations," according to a local businessman.
</P>
<P>
"We fully anticipate reunification of the motherland at an
early date, and Chinese people on both sides of the Straits are
currently enjoying harmonious relations," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
