<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Assets Reserves Drop in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's gross gold
and foreign exchange reserves fell to 32.6 billion Rand (5.3
billion U.S. Dollars) by July 31 from 33.4 billion Rand (5.5
billion U.S. Dollars) in June, the Reserve Bank said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The utilization of foreign credit lines at the end of July
amounted to 18.5 billion Rand (3 billion U.S. Dollars), up from
17 billion Rand (2.8 billion U.S. Dollars) in the previous month,
South African Press Association quoted the bank as reporting.
</P>
<P>
The outstanding oversold forward book of the bank remained at
25.2 billion U.S. Dollars by the end of July, compared to 25.3
billion U.S. Dollars in June.
</P>
<P>
The bank said that it had not intervened in the spot foreign
exchange market since July 3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
