<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Policeman Awakes from Coma after World Cup Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- French policeman Daniel Nivel, who
was clubbed over his head by German thugs six weeks ago during the
World Cup, has awoken from a coma on Monday, hospital officials
said Tuesday in Lille.
</P>
<P>
Nivel, 44, regained consciousness and was taken off a
respirator. He was expected to begin rehabilitation in the next
few weeks, Lille hospital said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"Daniel Nivel spends several hours per day in an armchair," the
statement said. "He suffers serious problems concerning
understanding and speech and will need extensive rehabilitation."
</P>
<P>
The hospital added that Nivel also was suffering from muscular
problems on his right side.
</P>
<P>
Nivel was attacked by a group of German fans shortly after a
June 21 World Cup match between Germany and Yugoslavia in this
northern French town where he was than guarding a police vehicle
near the stadium. He was hit on the back of the head with an iron
bar.
</P>
<P>
Four suspects are in custody in Germany, facing charges of
joint attempted murder and causing serious bodily harm as well as
disturbing the peace. Another suspect is being held in France.
</P>
</TEXT>
