<HEADLINE> Design Gallery Shops Re-launched in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Design Gallery shops displaying
more than 1,000 new varieties of products were re-launched here
Tuesday in a bid to further promote design professionalism of high
quality Hong Kong products.
</P>
<P>
These products range from high quality menswear and tableware
products to innovative household appliances, stationery sets and
electronic merchandise.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1991, the Design gallery under the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council (TDC) has already featured more than 59,000
products from over 1,600 companies in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the re-launching ceremony, Michael Sze, executive
director of the TDC, said that Hong Kong is becoming more
sophisticated, more cosmopolitan, a competitor among global
cities.
</P>
<P>
He said: "We are re-launching our three Design Gallery shops,
and highlighting their new and improved image to reflect that
increasing sophistication."
</P>
<P>
"Our shops will continue to encourage originality and
creativity in Hong Kong product design, as they have done in the
past seven years," he added.
</P>
<P>
Playing an important role in fostering local design creativity,
the Design Gallery shops are more than just retail outlets for
local consumers to purchase high quality local brandname products,
they have also successfully served as a one-stop sourcing center
for local and overseas buyers.
</P>
<P>
Sze presented six "Best Seller" awards of the Year 1997 to six
local companies at the re-launching ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
