<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong government has
approved a grant of 3 million HK dollars (385,000 U.S. dollars) to
the charity organization Salvation Army for emergency relief for
flood victims in China's inland area.
</P>
<P>
Together with the earlier grants of the same amount to World
Vision Hong Kong and to Hong Kong Red Cross, the Disaster Relief
Fund Advisory Committee, chaired by Administrative Secretary Anson
Chan, has approved in total 9 million HK dollars (1.2 million U.S.
dollars) from the Disaster Relief Fund for various relief projects
to assist the victims.
</P>
