<HEADLINE> Spanish Riders Quits Women's Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Spanish riders have dropped out
of the women's Tour de France in protest at the doping
investigations which tarnished the men's race.
</P>
<P>
"We take this measure because of the poor treatment received by
Spanish cyclists and teams in the Tour de France," the Spanish
Cycling Federation (SCF) said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
