<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed steady Tuesday on mild buying support
which capped a repeat of Monday's selling pressure.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index went up
0.17 of a point to 386.44, the all-share Emas Index dipped 0.37 of
a point to 99.33 while the Industrial Index rose 1.92 points to
812.40.
</P>
<P>
Losers thumped gainers by 321 to 193, while 182 counters were
unchanged and 226 others not traded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover stood at 76.532 million shares valued at
119.355 million ringgit (28.829 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
