<HEADLINE> Microsoft Fair to Promote Latest Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The world's largest software
provider, Microsoft, today announced it will host the Microsoft
TechEd and Solution Fair in Beijing Aug. 10-13.
</P>
<P>
According to Xia Peng, a manager of the department of
technological cooperation of Microsoft (China) Co., Ltd., the
latest technological developments in the industry are introduced
at this annual TechEd event.
</P>
<P>
This year, which is the fourth TechEd event in Beijing since
1994, 12 specialists from Microsoft headquarters in the United
States and five from Microsoft (China) will offer 30 courses in
the latest technologies such as Windows NT 5.0 and Visual Studio,
and the Year 2000 question.
</P>
<P>
The Solution Fair, held concurrently, will concentrate on
exhibiting local software solutions on Microsoft's platform that
were developed by the firm's Chinese partners, such as Founder
Group.
</P>
<P>
The events are the "Chinese version" of similar Microsoft
activities in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Attendance at the Beijing TechEd event this year is estimated
at 1,200.
</P>
<P>
The Solution Fair will be the first in China. Microsoft will
announce awards for the nine best local solutions out of 22
nominees.
</P>
<P>
The nominees were selected from products developed by 160
Microsoft Certified Software Providers.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft will also introduce its upcoming products, including
the much-anticipated Windows 98 Chinese version that is expected
to be on the market by the end of August.
</P>
<P>
The TechEd event will move on to Guangzhou and Hong Kong later
this month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
