<HEADLINE> Chengdu-Kunming Railway Held up by Mud-rock Flows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chengdu-Kunming Railway was
closed at 1:33 a.m. today because of mud and rock flows caused by
torrential rains in Miyi and Panzhihua in southwest China's
Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
Communications and cables were also discontinued. No casualties
have been reported yet.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that it will take two-to-three days to restore
traffic along the line, which runs between the capitals of Sichuan
and Yunnan provinces.
</P>
<P>
Related departments are taking steps to clear mud and rock on
the line, to provide lodging and medical services to affected
passengers, and to evacuate them.  
</P>
