<HEADLINE> Apartment House Collapses after Explosion in Berlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Up to eight people were feared buried
under the debris of a multi-storied apartment house which collapsed
early Tuesday morning in Berlin after a possible gas exlosion, German
media reports said.
</P>
<P>
The house, which has 19 registered tenants, was completely
destroyed in the explosion, leaving a hill of debris of about 10
meters high.
</P>
<P>
Firefighters said that they had managed to rescue out five people
and had been able to get into contact with another survivor still
trapped in the debris.
</P>
<P>
Another five tenants were said to not have been in the house when
the accident occurred.
</P>
<P>
About a hundred of rescuers had to work carefully on the scene for
fear of further collapse. Rescue dogs were also deployed to search for
possible survivors. enditem

