<HEADLINE> Economic Cooperation Booming in West China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Three neighboring provinces and an
autonomous region in western China are taking advantage of
convenient transportation to boost economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Situated at the juncture of central and western China, the
three provinces and an region, namely, Shaanxi, Gansu, Sichuan and
Ningxia, are connected by railway and highway arteries.
</P>
<P>
The economic cooperation zone they have formed covers an area
of 220,000 square kilometers with a total population of 35 million
in 86 counties, cities, and districts.
</P>
<P>
The zone produced nearly 100 billion yuan in GDP, 140 billion
yuan in industrial and agricultural output, and took in 6 billion
yuan in revenues in 1997, multiple increases over the figures in
the 1980s, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The area began co-sponsoring the West Trade Fair in 1989 and
has since hosted nine fairs which attracted over 200,000 domestic
and overseas traders, bringing in 36.5 billion yuan by 1997.
</P>
<P>
The fairs have greatly promoted exchanges of technology and
personnel, real estate projects and trade development in the area.
</P>
<P>
Experts forecast that the real estate sector will be the focus
of the upcoming 10th fair in September in Baoji city, Shaanxi
Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
