<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan Expects to Join WTO in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Jordan expects to become a member
of the the World Trade Organization (WTO) next year as it plans to
submit its membership application by mid-1999, a trade official
was quoted as saying Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Mohammad Halayqa, secretary-general of the Jordanian Ministry
of Industry and Trade, told the semi-official Jordan Times that
Jordnian government was encouraged by the results of the three
rounds of talks it has held with the WTO.
</P>
<P>
Jordan and the WTO concluded their second formal round of talks
last month after responding to the WTO's demands on abolishing the
Supply Ministry, fixing the ceiling on customs, and raising the
quality of agricultural products to international standards.
</P>
<P>
The two sides began their first contact in October 1996 and
held the first formal round of talks in July 1997.
</P>
<P>
As the two sides have reached a consensus and Jordan is ready
to accept WTO's criteria on the outstanding issues, the way for
the kingdom's accession to the organization would be smooth, said
Halayqa, who attended the talks.
</P>
<P>
One of the issues that remains unresolved is protecting the
intellectual property rights in the pharmaceutic field, which
Jordan has to do much work in the coming months, Halayqa said.
</P>
<P>
The strategy that Jordan will adopt in dealing with the issue
is to hold bilateral talks with the main trade partners to win
broad-based support before holding formal meetings with the WTO,
he added.
</P>
<P>
He noted that it has reached an agreement with the European
Union, in which the kingdom was granted a three-year grace period
to implement laws on protection intellectual property rights for
its pharmaceutical industry.
</P>
<P>
To assist Jordan in its bid for the WTO membership, the United
Nations Development Programme has launched a 300,000 U.S. dollar
project to train Jordanian negotiators in developing technical and
mediation skills for talks with the WTO. 
</P>
</TEXT>
