<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flower Business Booming in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua)-- Flowers and potted landscapes are
growing in popularity in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
This spring the city's flower market prospered with a record
daily sales volume of 500,000 bouquets.
</P>
<P>
Peng Zhigang, owner of an inn near Zhongguancun in western
Beijing, turned his inn into a floral shop at the beginning of
this year. His flowers sold very well in April and early May when
Beijing University was observing its centennial and a computer
festival was held in Zhongguancun, a district known for
electronics products.
</P>
<P>
According to the Beijing Flower Association, the city now has
more than 250 floral shops and three large wholesale floral
markets. The sales volume last year was 96 million bouquets and
that of this year is expected to go up by 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Flowers have become daily consumer goods rather than festival
luxuries for more and more Beijing people. Now people take flowers
instead of fruits or cakes when visiting friends and relatives.
</P>
<P>
More than 6,000 overseas corporations and 200 restaurants are
also big consumers of flowers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
