<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Take Legal Action Against Doctors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government will
take legal action against doctors who have not returned to the
country after completing their special training abroad, a senior
official announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Health and Indigenous Medicine Minister Nimal Siripala De Silva
told local reporters that 26 such doctors are yet to return and
the ministry will give them a period of one month to return.
</P>
<P>
The government has taken this decision in view of the shortage
of specialists in public hospitals. The minister said these
doctors have to return before August 30, if they are unable to
return on or before the given date the ministry will take legal
action against them.
</P>
<P>
It was said that many Sri Lanka's doctors who have gone to
England and France for training have not returned after completing
the training. 
</P>
</TEXT>
