<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kingdom of Animals Exhibit to Open in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 vivid specimens
and 500 photographs of rare animals will illustrate the charm of
the kingdom of animals starting in mid-August in this capital city
of southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
This standing exhibition consists of more than 1,000 rare
animals selected from 500,000 animal species, including birds,
amphibians, fish and insects. Many of these animals are specific
to Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan is rich in animal resources, with its vertebrate species
accounting for 51 percent of the country's total. The province
also has more than 10,000 species of the country's total listed
insects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
