<DOCNO> XIE19980804.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Oldest Stone-carved Urban Map Found in Guangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A stone-carved map produced about
700 years ago has been found in Guilin, a picturesque city and a
famous tourist attraction in southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
The map is believed to be the world's oldest on urban plane
figure, Chinese archeologists said.
</P>
<P>
The 2.9 meter-long and 2.98 meter-wide map depicts the general
situation of Guilin during the Southern Song Dynasty (1127-1279),
when it was an important military and trade center in southwest
China.
</P>
<P>
The map was produced in 1272, and was one of the only two
preserved urban maps dating back to the Southern Song Dynasty. The
other was about Suzhou in east China, archeologists said.
</P>
<P>
"The map first revealed the karst topography in the world, and
it is the oldest military map preserved intact in China," said Tan
Fasheng, director of the Research Department of the Guilin Museum.
</P>
<P>
"In producing the map, the unknown authors had used different
scales, which coordinate between the city shapes and the
landscapes, and highlights important city parts," said Ma Chong, a
researcher from the city's Place Names Office.
</P>
<P>
The map has 36 marks among which emerged model symbols, an
evidence of the advanced level of cartography in ancient China,
archeologists said.
</P>
<P>
The map has 146 language marks, most of them for military
purposes, and the map shows the city was strongly fortified, said
Su Hongji, an archeologist with the Guilin Museum.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980804.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Visa Talks Undergoing Between Mozambique, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Negotiations on visa exemption
between Mozambique and Zimbabwe have been going well, said
Mozambican Minister of Planning and Finance Tomaz Salomao.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the remarks during his recent inspection
trip to the central Manica Province bordering Zimbabwe, the daily
Noticias newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The visa exemption talks will greatly facilitate the flows of
investment, personnel and materials between the two countries,
said Salomao.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican minister noted that the agreement on visa
exemption reached between Mozambique and Malawi about two years
ago has borne positive fruits.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that after an agreement is reached for visa
exemption between his country and Zimbabwe, similar negotiations
will be initiated with other southern African countries.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that in the last two months, some 60
Zimbabwean farmers visited the central, southern and northern
parts of Manica Province to find out the possibilities of
investing in agriculture, husbandry and agro-industry in the
area.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government of Manica has reportedly issued a
decree in which it offers preferential status for those
Zimbabwean farmers willing to invest in the reaches of Zambeze
River. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
