<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Transportation Improved in Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Ten years ago, tourists found it
inconvenient to go to Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region since there
was only one railway and one small airport linking it with the
rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
Now tourists flocking to visit this only autonomous region of
Chinese Muslims find travel choices by air, land and water are
plentiful because of marked improvement in transportation
conditions.
</P>
<P>
For six consecutive years, highways in the region have been
expanding at an annual rate of 330 kilometers, bringing the total
roadways to 8,700 kilometers. A highway network featuring 13
national and provincial roads and more than 100 county and
township roads has been formed.
</P>
<P>
While only the Baotou-Lanzhou Railway passes through the
region, a new electrified railway has opened plus its first
regional rail, extending the total length to 837 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Before 1997, Ningxia remained the only region in the country
incapable of accommodating large aircraft. This situation ended in
September when Hedong Airport, capable of handling Boeing 747
aircraft, went into operation in the regional capital of Yinchuan.
</P>
<P>
Travelers in the region also can use six highway bridges across
the Yellow River, the major waterway in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
