<DOCNO> XIE19980804.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Private Investments for Tianjin Industrial Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A new-tech industrial park in the
port city of Tianjin is attracting an increasing amount of
individual investment.
</P>
<P>
Of the 130 million yuan of the total capital of the 246 firms
newly registered in the park this year, private entrepreneurs
account for 108 million yuan (13 million U.S. dollars),
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts attribute the growth in private investment to
several factors including further relaxed government policies for
the private economy, policies encouraging laid-off workers from
state-owned enterprises to play their role in economic
development, more technicians applying their research to wider
fields, and an enhanced awareness of investment in
technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
