<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Township Enterprise Buys French Garment Maker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At a cost of 10 million yuan (1.2 million U.S. dollars), the
Hengbai Group, a leading textile producer of Shaoxing County,
became a producer of the "Mallard" suit of France. The acquisition
also turned it into the third largest suit-maker in Zhejiang
Province.
</P>
<P>
Xia Baichao, president of Hengbai, said his firm has already
invested 100 million yuan in importing a first-class suit-making
production line which will be used for producing 150,000 Mallard
suits a year. The group also plans to open franchises and special
counters for the Mallard suits in 50 major Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
The Hengbai Group is one of the largest textile enterprises in
Shaoxing, which is itself a leading textile production center in
China.
</P>
<P>
The Mallard production base was set up in Shaoxing three years
ago, however, the former owner reportedly ran into difficulties in
marketing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
