<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' aggregate earning
from exports in the first six months this year increased by 18.8
percent to 13.904 billion U.S. dollars from 11.700 billion dollars
in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
A report from the National Statistics Office showed that total
earning for June alone reached 2.389 billion dollars for a 12.2
percent growth over 2.129 billion dollars in the same month of
1997.
</P>
<P>
It showed that shipments of electronics and components, still
the top dollar earner with a 51.5 percent share, grew by 46.0
percent to 1.230 billion dollars in June from 842.59 million
dollars in the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Manufactured goods posted an 18.9 percent increase in sales,
which reached 2,140.55 million dollars in June from 1,800.17
million dollars a year earlier. This major export group accounted
for 89.6 percent of the total receipts.
</P>
<P>
Exports to the United States amounted to 882.18 million dollars
in June, posting a 19.8 percent growth from 736.10 million dollars
a year earlier and accounting for 36.9 percent of the total, it
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
