<DOCNO> XIE19980804.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Province Builds Water Conservancy Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a water
conservancy project is under way at the Feilai Gorge on the
Beijiang River, a tributary of the Pearl River in south China's
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
With a reservoir with a holding capacity of 1.9 billion cubic
meters, the project will be a multi-purpose facility with flood
control as its main function.
</P>
<P>
The river was cut off on August 1 by a dam, on which four
generators with a combined generating capacity of 140,000 kw will
be installed.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the project began in October 1994 and it is
expected to be completed in September 1999. It will cost some five
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
When completed, the project will play a vital role in
protecting the economically developed Pearl River Delta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
