<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank of China Intensifies Support of Exporters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) today
vowed to increase its support of the foreign trade sector by
promising five billion yuan in financing to a leading foreign
trade company.
</P>
<P>
The bank clinched a cooperative agreement with the China
National Metals and Minerals Import and Export Corporation
(Minmetals) today, promising it huge financing this year and next
year in forms of long-term local-currency and
foreign-exchange loans, bill acceptance, and guarantees.
</P>
<P>
Financing is extremely important to foreign trade companies at
present because of the difficulties they have encountered during
the sweeping Asian financial crisis, that began in July last year.
</P>
<P>
The nation's foreign trade sector will need to grow ten percent
this year to support the economic growth goal of eight percent.
</P>
<P>
The foreign trade sector has always been given top priority in
receiving loans from the BOC, and the bank's outstanding loans to
these foreign trade companies had reached 234.6 billion yuan by the
end of June.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the bank will also provide
Minmetals with financial services such as consulting,
representation in domestic and international settlements and
guarantees.
</P>
<P>
It will also aid the corporation, a large enterprise group
whose core business is international trade, in the fields of trade,
investment, real estate and financial expansion, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
Minmetal's annual trade volume has for years been among the top
five of China's 500 largest specialized foreign trade firms.
</P>
<P>
The BOC this year signed lending agreements valued at more than
42 billion yuan with dozens of large enterprises in an effort to
boost national economic growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
