<HEADLINE> Floods Claim 20 Lives in Sichuan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Flooding over the past few days
in southwest China's Sichuan Province had claimed 20 lives by
Monday night, with two others missing and 370 reported injured.
</P>
<P>
The latest report from the provincial relief office said that
torrential rains have caused flooding in 22 counties,
affecting 22,500 hectares of crops and destroying some 6,550 houses.
</P>
<P>
The year's fifth rainstorm hit 8 cities and prefectures
including Chengdu, Leshan, Zigong and Yibin, causing water levels
at the upper reaches of the Yangtze River and main tributaries to
reach the danger line, and resulting in mud and rock flows and
landslides in some places.
</P>
<P>
Yibin city was seriouly hit, with 8 townships flooded, 8 people
dead, and more than 300 others stranded. Rescue work is underway.
</P>
<P>
Jianwei County is another example, where some 30 townships
and 250,000 people were affected, with 8 dead, two missing, and
economic losses estimated at 40 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Rescue work is also continuing in Jianwei, sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
