<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Colombo Port to Be Further Developed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Port of Colombo will
be further developed following improvement of the Queen Elizabeth
Quay (QEQ), according to Sri Lankan port Authority (SLPA) sources
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to improve the QEQ was initialized recently by the
project promoters -- South Asia Gateway Terminal Ltd. (SAGT) and
the (SLPA), the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the development project will enhance QEQ's
capacity to one million Twenty Foot Equivalent Units (TEUs) from
the present figure of 250,000 TEUs at a cost of 200 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
A Consortium led by the International Finance Corporation of
the World Bank, The Asian Development Bank and the Commonwealth
Development Corporation have been working to procure finance for
the project.
</P>
<P>
Port users have stressed the need to expedite the development
of QEQ to improve cargo handling in the Colombo port and
effectively face growing challenges from competing Asian regional
ports, the sources added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
