<HEADLINE> Testud Survives First-round at WTA Tour Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Sandrine Testud survived a
first-round scare to enter the second round of the WTA Tour
tournament at San Diego, California, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Testud, ranked 13th in the world, rallied to beat American
amateur Alexandra Stevenson 4-6, 6-2, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old Stevenson showed maturity beyond her years
during the match and attacked well with both forehand and backhand.
</P>
<P>
After taking the first set, Stevenson held break points in
Testud's first two service games of the second set.
</P>
<P>
But Stevenson faded later in the match, conceding the final 10
points of the second set and earned just one point in the third.
</P>
<P>
In other first-round matches played on Monday, Iva Majoli of
Croatia beat Alexandra Fusai of France 7-6 (7-1), 6-3 and another
French player Mary Pierce rolled over Barbara Paulus of Austria
6-3, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
American Lisa Raymond also advanced into the second round when
Elena Likhovtseva of Russia retired with a left thigh strain as
Raymond led 6-2, 5-1. 
</P>
