<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka To Host Asian Congress Of Architects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka will host the Asian
Congress of Architects in Colombo from November 10 to 15 this
year, in which around 500 international delegates from 15 Asian
countries are expected to participate.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Congress of Architects (ACA) is the meeting of the
Architects Regional Council of Asia (ARCA) that takes place once
in two years in a member country since 1980.
</P>
<P>
The theme of this congress is the "Redefining the role of
Architects to face the challenges of the 21st Century," sources
from the Sri Lankan Council of Architects said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ARCA is consisting of the presidents of the national
institutes of architects in the Asian region.
</P>
<P>
It serves as an extension for each member Institute's regional
program and relations. It meets annually to deliberate and give
collective direction and representation to matters that affect the
architectural profession in the region. 
</P>
