more than 20 billion Rand (3.3 billion U.S. Dollars) in foreign
exchange last year, a new record in the sector, Environment and
Tourism Minister Pallo Jordan said Monday. (SAfrica-Tourism)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japan's foreign exchange reserves rose by 1,624
million U.S. dollars in July from the previous month to 207,498
million dollars, the Finance Ministry said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The increase follows June's fall of 1,101 million dollars,
which was the first decline since April and the result of
dollar-selling intervention by the Japanese monetary authorities
to prop up the falling yen. (Japan-Foreign Reserves)
</P>
