<HEADLINE> More Fighting, Casualties Reported in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Armed clashes between Serb
police and ethnic Albanians have flared up again in southwest
Kosovo and casualties have been reported on both sides.
</P>
<P>
In a Monday-Tuesday fight against a charge of ethnic Albanian
militants, the Serb police successfully defended their position
and killed a dozen militants, the information center in Pristina
said.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians also attacked a Serb police post Sunday on the
road linking Dechani and Djakovicha; two policemen were killed and
two others were injured.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslavian military troops stationed at villages outside
Djakovicha were also attacked by ethnic Albanian armed forces
these past two days, the information center said.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic tension in Kosovo, a province of the Republic of Serbia
of the federal Yugoslavia, has been mounting as ethnic Albanians'
seek for independence led to armed clashes.
</P>
<P>
Between January 1 and July 27, ethnic Albanians had kidnapped
171 civilians and 10 policemen, the center said, adding that 118
civilians and all 10 policemen were still being held hostage and
their safety in question. 
</P>
</TEXT>
