<HEADLINE> Nicaraguan GDP Up 6 Percent in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- The Nicaraguan gross domestic
product (GDP) is expected to increase by 6 percent, the Central
Bank of Nicaragua said.
</P>
<P>
This year's GDP should climb to 1.1 billion cordobas (about 110
million U.S. dollars) more than in 1997, which amounted to 21.43
billion cordobas.
</P>
<P>
Noel Ramirez, an official from the Central Bank, said his
country will continue to keep its leading position in so far as
economic development in Central America is concerned.
</P>
<P>
He said the rise in agricultural products will contribute to
the GDP increase. Agricultural products are expected to be up by
16 percent in 1998. 
</P>
