<HEADLINE> Shanghai Enlarges Lu Xun Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Municipality has begun
repairing and enlarging the Lu Xun Museum in the city.
</P>
<P>
The 2,000-square-meter museum opened to public in 1956 in
memory of Lu Xun (1881-1936), a famous Chinese revolutionary
writer. Since that time, more than 10 million people from China
and abroad have visited the museum.
</P>
<P>
The new section of the museum will be a two-storey traditional
Chinese residential house with a total floor space of 4,683
square meters. It will include two exhibition halls and a lecture
room.
</P>
<P>
The writer's hometown of Shaoxing in east China's Zhejiang
Province has donated 550,000 yuan for the project, which
will be completed next September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
