<HEADLINE> Large Amount of Stimulant Drugs Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized a
total of five million stimulant drug tablets in northern Shan
state of the country last month, official The New Light of Myanmar
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The stimulant drugs were confiscated in Nawnghkio on July 22 by
a combined team of the Myanmar Defense Services Intelligence unit
and the Special Anti-Drug Squad who searched a car coming from a
Myanmar border town.
</P>
<P>
Two were arrested involved in the drug trafficking, it said.
</P>
<P>
The two were also reported to have met a Thai citizen drug
dealer at the border town and received some 2.5 million Kyats
(8,333 U.S. dollars) for carrying the stimulant drugs to Mandalay,
second largest city in central part of the country.
</P>
<P>
The local police authorities have taken action against them,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
In June, the Myanmar authorities also seized 1.49 million
tablets of stimulant drugs in the country along with 43 kilograms
(kg) heroin and 2,033 kg opium, according to earlier official
report. 
</P>
