<HEADLINE> Jakarta Needs Huge Money to Renovate Damaged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesia's capital of
Jakarta needs at least 10 trillion rupiah (850 million U.S.
dollars) to renovate damaged shopping centers rampaged through
during the mid-May unrests, an official was quoted by local press
Tuesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
The renovations are needed to restore the capital's image,
fractured by the waves of lootings and arson during the two days
of rioting, Deputy Governor for Administrative Affairs Abdul Kahfi
told a meeting here Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said the Indonesian government was blamed for being unable
to protect the public and their properties from the raging mob
during the riots in May 13 and 14.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that over 5,000 shops and homes of
ethnic-Chinese were burned and looted, and 1,193 people were
killed during the May riots in Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
Kahfi acknowledged that though the riot occurred three months
ago, its impact is still influencing public life until today.
</P>
