"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Beneficiaries of Chinese servicemen killed in the line of
duty will be cared for financially under newly adopted
regulations.
</P>
<P>
A beneficiary will receive, in addition to the soldier's
pension, a guaranteed sum 10 times greater than the pension.
</P>
<P>
The regulations, which also insure all members of the People's
Liberation Army against injuries and death, took effect on August
1, the Army Day.
</P>
<P>
-- China's large enterprises continued to demonstrate their
leading position in the national economy with good results from
the latest quarterly official quality inspection of products.
</P>
<P>
The results, released yesterday by the China State Bureau of
Quality and Technical Supervision, put the country's large
manufacturers more than 25.1 percentage points higher than small
factories.  
