<HEADLINE> Indonesian Government to Seriously Probe May Riot: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
taken serious measures to investigate the acts of violence during
the May riots, local press Tuesday quoted Chairman of the Joint
Fact-finding Team Marzuki Darusman as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The formation of the Joint Fact-finding Team is proof of the
government's seriousness in uncovering the acts of violence,
including rapes of ethnic Chinese women", Marzuki told a group of
Taiwanese women human rights activists here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Marzuki explained his guests that the joint team, which was
formed on July 23, involves various groups such as government
officials, military officers, non-governmental organizations,
lawyers and women's organizations.
</P>
<P>
"A thorough investigation is being conducted," he said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia saw the worst looting and rioting in decades in
Jakarta and other cities from May 13 to 15. About 1,200 lives were
claimed, and thousands of buildings and vehicles were damaged and
burnt. It was reported that the total number of victims of rape
and sexual harassment from the rioting reached 168.
</P>
<P>
When asked about the latest findings of the joint team, Marzuki
said the team was still collecting data and information from
various sources.
</P>
<P>
"Later we will evaluate the information and then decide on
concrete measures, such as questioning witness," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
