<HEADLINE> Costa Rican President Opposes Gay Congress. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 3 (xinhua) -- Costa Rican President Miguel
Angel Rodriguez expressed his opposition to a gay congress
scheduled for later this month in Quepos Beach some 140 kilometers
from the capital city of San Jose.
</P>
<P>
He said such an event should not be authorized, saying that if
the organizing committee insists on carrying it out, they will
have to come up with the proper requirements.
</P>
<P>
The president's remarks were in response to a question raised
by Monseigneur Roman Arrieta, head of the Catholic Church in Costa
Rica, who made public his opposition to the gay conference on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez said that the authorities will give no permission to
make this kind of events public.
</P>
<P>
In view of strong opposition, "Triangulo Rosa," the gay
conference organizing party, said there will be a change of
location of the meeting to a "secret site."
</P>
<P>
The event has been promoted over the past few months around the
world through Internet, and many sectors in the country have
protested against its publicity. 
</P>
