<HEADLINE> OAU Says Badme is Ethiopia's Land: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 3 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Minister Seyoum
Mesfin said Monday the Organization of African Unity (OAU) has
affirmed that Badme and its environs were under Ethiopian
administration prior to the Eritrean occupation on May 12.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by Mesfin upon his arrival here from a
two-day OAU ministerial meeting on Ethio-Eritrean border dispute
in Burkina Faso.
</P>
<P>
Seyoum told local journalists that "the OAU ministerial report
established beyond doubts the fundamental fact that the disputed
Badme and Shiraro areas were under Ethiopian administration
before the Eritrean invasion on May 12, 1998."
</P>
<P>
Seyoum said the report by the Ministerial Committee of the
Peace Mission will be presented to the OAU mandated heads of
state who are expected to hold consultations and pass decisions
in two or three weeks time.
</P>
<P>
He said the Ministerial Committee had separate talks with both
Ethiopian and Eritrean delegations on their respective stance on
the solution to the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The committee, he said, has prepared a report on the basis of
evidences by the ambassadors and briefing of the delegations, a
copy of which has given to both countries.
</P>
<P>
The result of the Ouagadougou meeting has come out with the
truth, the Ethiopian foreign minister asserted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
